  "text": "The inter-segment data transfer mechanism described in Sec 4.4 requires up to two rows to be activated in the same subarray at once, necessitating a second row decoder. However, since one of the two activated rows is always in the near segment, this second row decoder only needs to address rows in the near segment. For a near segment with 32 rows, a scheme that splits the 5 (log 2 32) near segment address bits into 3-bit and 2-bit sets requires 12 additional wires to be routed to each subarray (3:8 predecoding + 2:4 predecoding). The corresponding die-size penalty is 0.33%, calculated based on the total die-size and wire-pitch derived from Vogelsang [39, [CITATION_1] .",
